						<div class="postbody">I'd say what's going on looks something like this:<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$0000&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$2000&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$4000&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$6000<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; or $8000&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$a000&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$c000&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;$e000<br />-- Mode 3 -----------------------------------------<br />PRG_RAM_A |&nbsp; $5114&nbsp; |&nbsp; $5115&nbsp; |&nbsp; $5116&nbsp; |&nbsp; $5113&nbsp; |<br />PRG_ROM_A |&nbsp; $5114&nbsp; |&nbsp; $5115&nbsp; |&nbsp; $5116&nbsp; |&nbsp; $5117&nbsp; |<br />-- Mode 2 -----------------------------------------<br />PRG_RAM_A |&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;$5115&gt; |&nbsp; $5116&nbsp; |&nbsp; $5113&nbsp; |<br />PRG_ROM_A |&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;$5115&gt; |&nbsp; $5116&nbsp; |&nbsp; $5117&nbsp; |<br />-- Mode 1 -----------------------------------------<br />PRG_RAM_A |&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;$5115&gt; |&nbsp; &nbsp;???&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; $5113&nbsp; |<br />PRG_ROM_A |&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;$5115&gt; |&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;$5117&gt; |<br />-- Mode 0 -----------------------------------------<br />PRG_RAM_A |&nbsp; &nbsp;???&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;???&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp;???&nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; $5113&nbsp; |<br />PRG_ROM_A |&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&lt;&lt;$5117&gt;&gt; |<br /></div>The ???s are both unknown and due to how the chip enables work, can't be made relevant without a custom PCB. But I'd hunch that in the $8000-$DFFF range, PRG_RAM_A and PRG_ROM_A are the same value.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">If this is true, why not combine registers $5113 and $5117 and use the RAM/ROM bit?<br /><br />Answer: Because both ram and rom are enabled at the same time with independent pages because of that.<br /></div>Bingo.</div>

